MethodHandleProxy$LegacyVersion` is explicitly guarded for pre-module Java runtimes:\n\n```java\nClass.forName(\"java.lang.Module\");\nthrow new RuntimeException(\"Must not be used when modules are available\");\n```\n\n- Therefore, on Java 9+ / GraalVM 25, `LegacyVersion` construction is intentionally rejected before its `resolve(...)` method can run.\n- The remaining uncovered call sites are inside `LegacyVersion.resolve(...)`, which is only reachable on Java 8-like runtimes where `java.lang.Module` is absent.\n\nI left the active-class-dedicated test in place:\n\n`tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/MethodHandleProxyInnerLegacyVersionTest.java`\n\nIt exercises the closest supported public API path: interface default-method invocation through Mockito’s proxy mock maker. I also fixed the access issue by making the nested interface public.\n\nI did not force coverage through direct reflection, internal construction, fake/shadow classes, or classloader/JDK manipulation because those would violate the task rules and Native Image execution contract. No metadata files were edited.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01fcf1ab54630e51016a3a9ec3ad1c819384581b875bef430e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 258, "output": 1215, "cacheRead": 41472, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42945, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782226602184, "responseId": "resp_01fcf1ab54630e51016a3a9eab2b6481939f0153d16bd89bbd"}}
